data.name: welcomeText.Text
data.value: Welcome to iBreak, the most versatile jailbreak tool on the market. The purpose of this program is to help you navigate the sometimes tough process of jailbreaking. In the next 5 steps, we will walk you through the process of downloading the files, prepping the environment and jailbreaking the device. Let’s go!

data.name: walkthroughText3.Text
data.value:
This step will guide you through the process of using the tool iBreak selected for you. Simply follow along.
1. Click "Jailbreak." 2. Power off you device and connect it to your computer. 3. Read the information that is given to you. Follow the instructions and then click "Next." 4. Carefully follow the prompts and the timers given to you by the tool. 5. If your device powers off or reboots, wait for it to complete and then close the tool.
Click Next below when you have completed the steps listed above.

data.name: walkthroughText2.Text
data.value:
This step will guide you through the process of using the tool iBreak selected for you. Simply follow along.
1. First, navigate to http://www.felixbruns.de/iPod/firmware/ and download the firmware that corresponds with your device and software version. It is a large file, so it may take some time. 2. Once the file has been downloaded, if it is not an .ipsw file, rename the extension of the file from ".zip" to ".ipsw". 3. In the jailbreak tool, click "Browse" and navigate to and select the file above. 4. Make sure to carefully read the information that may pop up after selecting the file, and then click "Next." 3. Verify that "Install Cydia" is checked, and then click "Next." 4. Follow the instructions that the jailbreak tool provides you, and then click "Next." 5. Carefully follow the prompts and the timers given to you by the tool. 6. If your device powers off or reboots, wait for it to complete and then close the tool.
Click Next below when you have completed the steps listed above.

data.name: walkthroughText1.Text
data.value:
This step will guide you through the process of using the tool iBreak selected for you. Simply follow along.
1. Click "No" when prompted about jailbreaking an AppleTV. 2. Power off you device and connect it to your computer. 3. Click "Prepare to Jailbreak (DFU)" 4. Follow the directions given to you by the tool. If you feel like you need to start over, click the "reset" button under the timer. 5. If your device powers off or reboots, wait for it to complete and then close the tool.
Click Next below when you have completed the steps listed above.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value:
iBreak has determined the correct jailbreak tool for your specified device. It is now ready for you to launch.
After pressing the button below, please advance to the next step for a walkthrough of the jailbreak process.

data.name: tetheringText1.Text
data.value: There is no untethered jailbreak tool for your device at this time. This means that you will need to connect your device to your computer for it to boot it if it is ever restarted or is drained of battery.

data.name: walkthroughText4.Text
data.value:
This step will guide you through the process of using the tool iBreak selected for you. Simply follow along.
1. Click "Ok," then click "Close Credits," and finally click on the forward arrow. 2. First, navigate to http://www.felixbruns.de/iPod/firmware/ and download the firmware that corresponds with your device and software version. It is a large file, so it may take some time. 3. Once the file has been downloaded, if it is not an .ipsw file, rename the extension of the file from ".zip" to ".ipsw". 4. Now in the jailbreak tool, either browse to the file that you saved above or drag it onto the window. 4. Carefully follow the prompts given to you by the tool. 5. If your device powers off or reboots, wait for it to complete, and then close the tool.
Click Next below when you have completed the steps listed above.
